of Philosophical Logic</em>, 8: 219&ndash;241.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1999, &ldquo;What not? A defence of
dialetheic theory of negation&rdquo;, in Gabbay and Wansing 1999:
101&ndash;120.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2002, &ldquo;Paraconsistent logic&rdquo;,
in: D. Gabbay and F. Guenthner (eds.), <em>Handbook of Philosophical
Logic</em> (Volume 6), 2nd edition, Dordrecht: Kluwer,
287&ndash;393.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2006, <em>Doubt Truth to be a Liar</em>,
Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2008, <em>An Introduction to Non-Classical
Logic: From Ifs to Is</em>, second edition, Cambridge: Cambridge
University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2010, &ldquo;The logic of the
<em>catuskoti</em>&rdquo;, <em>Comparative Philosophy</em>, 1:
24&ndash;54.</li>

<li>Prior, A. N., 2006, &ldquo;Negation&rdquo;, in D.M. Borchert
(ed.), <em>Encyclopedia of Philosophy, 2<sup>nd</sup> ed.</em>, Vol.
6, 522&ndash;530, New York: Macmillan.</li>

<li>Pun&#269;och&aacute;&#345;, V. and I. Sedl&aacute;r, 2022,
&ldquo;Routley star in information-based semantics&rdquo;,
<em>Electronic Proceedings in Theoretical Computer Science</em>, 358:
285&ndash;297.</li>

<li>Pullum, G., 2002, &ldquo;Negation&rdquo;, Chapter 9 in R.
Huddleston &amp; G. Pullum, <em>The Cambridge Grammar of the English
Language</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>Quine, W. V. O., 1960, <em>Word and Object</em>, Cambridge, MA:
MIT Press.</li>

<li>Ramsey, F. P., 1927, &ldquo;Facts and Propositions&rdquo;,
<em>Proceedings of the Aristotelian Society (Suppl. Vol.)</em>, 7:
153&ndash;170.</li>

<li>Rauszer, C., 1980, <em>An Algebraic and Kripke-style Approach to a
Certain Extension of Intuitionistic Logic</em>, Dissertationes
Mathematicae 167, Institute of Mathematics, Polish Academy of
Sciences, Warsaw.</li>

<li>Restall, G., 1993, &ldquo;How to Be Really Contraction
Free&rdquo;, <em>Studia Logica</em>, 52: 381&ndash;391.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1999, &ldquo;Negation in relevant logics
(How I stopped worrying and learned to love the Routley Star)&rdquo;,
in Gabbay and Wansing 1999: 53&ndash;76.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2000, <em>An Introduction to Substructural
Logics</em>, London: Routledge, London.</li>

<li>Ripley, D., 2009, <em>Negation in Natural Language</em>, Ph.D.
Dissertation, Philosophy Department, University of North
Carolina/Chapel Hill
 [<a href="https://cdr.lib.unc.edu/record/uuid:8b50aebb-e71a-48a7-881e-d863d2e77ce1" target="other">Ripley 2009 available online</a>].</li>
 
<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011a, &ldquo;Contradictions at the
borders&rdquo;, in R. Nouwen, R. van Rooij, U. Sauerland and H.-C.
Schmitz (eds.), <em>Vagueness in Communication</em>, 169&ndash;188,
Berlin: Springer.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011b, &ldquo;Negation, denial, and
rejection&rdquo;, <em>Philosophy Compass</em>, 6: 622&ndash;629.</li>

<li>Rooth, M., 1992, &ldquo;A theory of focus interpretation&rdquo;,
<em>Natural Language Semantics</em>, 1: 75&ndash;116.</li>

<li>Routley, R. and V. Routley, 1972, &ldquo;Semantics for first
degree entailment&rdquo;, <em>No&ucirc;s</em>, 6: 335&ndash;59.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1985, &ldquo;Negation and
contradiction&rdquo;, <em>Revista Colombiana de
Matem&aacute;ticas</em>, 19: 201&ndash;230.</li>

<li>Rumfitt, I., 2000, &ldquo;&rdquo;Yes&ldquo; and
&rdquo;no&ldquo;&rdquo;, <em>Mind</em>, 109: 781&ndash;823.</li>

<li>Russell, B., 1905, &ldquo;On denoting&rdquo;, <em>Mind</em>, 14:
479&ndash;93.</li>

<li>Ruytenbeek, N, S. Verheyen, and B. Spector, 2017,
&ldquo;Asymmetric inference toward the antonym: Experiments into the
polarity and morphology of negated adjectives&rdquo;, <em>Glossa</em>,
2(1): 92.</li>

<li>S&aacute;nchez Valencia, V., 1994, &ldquo;Monotonicity in medieval
logic&rdquo;, <em>Language and Cognition</em>, 4: 161&ndash;174.</li>

<li>Sandu, G., 1994, &ldquo;Some aspects of negation in
English&rdquo;, <em>Synthese</em>, 99: 345&ndash;360.</li>

<li>Sbardolini, G., 2024, &ldquo;On the origin of negation&rdquo;,
<em>Erkenntnis</em>, 89: 2233&ndash;2252.</li>

<li>Segerberg, K., 1971, <em>An Essay in Classical Modal Logic</em>,
vol. 1&ndash;3, Uppsala Philosophical Studies, Uppsala
University.</li>

<li>Seuren, P. and D. Jaspers, 2014, &ldquo;Logico-cognitive structure
in the lexicon&rdquo;, <em>Language</em>, 90: 607&ndash;43.</li>

<li>Shaw, J.L., 1988, &ldquo;The Ny&acirc;ya on double
negation&rdquo;, <em>Notre Dame Journal of Formal Logic</em>, 29:
139&ndash;54.</li>

<li>Shramko, Y., 2005, &ldquo;Dual intuitionistic logic and a variety
of negations: the logic of scientific research&rdquo;, <em>Studia
Logica</em>, 80: 347&ndash;367.</li>

<li>Shramko, Y. and H. Wansing, 2011, <em>Truth and Falsehood. An
Inquiry into Generalized Logical Values</em>, Dordrecht:
Springer.</li>

<li>Smiley, T., 1993, &ldquo;Can contradictions be true?, I&rdquo;,
<em>Proceedings of the Aristotelian Society</em>, 67:
17&ndash;34.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1996, &ldquo;Rejection&rdquo;,
<em>Analysis</em>, 56: 1&ndash;9.</li>

<li>Sommers, F. and G. Englebretsen, 2000, <em>An Invitation to Formal
Reasoning: The Logic of Terms</em>, Aldershot: Ashgate.</li>

<li>Speranza, J.L. and L. Horn, 2012, &ldquo;A brief history of
negation&rdquo;, in Gabbay, Pelletier, and Woods 2012:
127&ndash;174.</li>

<li>Spruyt, J., 1989, <em>Peter of Spain on Composition and
Negation</em>, Nijmegen: Ingenium.</li>

<li>Steinert-Threlkeld, Shane, 2019, &ldquo;Quantifiers in natural
language optimize the simplicity/informativeness trade-off&rdquo;, in
Julian J. Schl&ouml;der, Dean McHugh, and Floris Roelofsen,
<em>Proceedings of the 22nd Amsterdam Colloquium</em>,
513&ndash;522.</li>

<li>Strawson, P.F., 1950, &ldquo;On referring&rdquo;, <em>Mind</em>,
59: 320&ndash;44.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1952, <em>Introduction to Logical
Theory</em>, London: Methuen.</li>

<li>de Swart, H., 2011, <em>Expression and Interpretation of Negation:
An OT Typology</em>, Dordrecht: Springer.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2020, &ldquo;Double negation readings&rdquo;, in
D&eacute;prez and Espinal (eds.) 2020, 479&ndash;496.</li>

<li>Todd, P., 2020, &ldquo;The problem of future contingents: scoping
out a solution&rdquo;, <em>Synthese</em>, 197: 5051&ndash;5072.</li>

<li>Tottie, G. and A. Neukom-Hermann, 2010, &ldquo;Quantifier-negation
interaction in English: A corpus linguistic study of
<em>all...not</em> constructions&rdquo;. In Horn 2010b:
149&ndash;185.</li>

<li>Tranchini, L., 2021, &ldquo;La n&eacute;gation&rdquo;, in F.
Poggiolesi and P. Wagner (eds.), <em>Pr&eacute;cis de Philosophie de
la Logique</em>, Paris: &Eacute;ditions de la Sorbonne,
253&ndash;301.</li>

<li>Uegaki, W., 2024, &ldquo;The informativity/complexity trade-off in
the domain of Boolean connectives&rdquo;, <em>Linguistic Inquiry</em>,
55: 174&ndash;196.</li>

<li>Vakarelov, D., 1977, <em>Theory of Negation in Certain Logical
Systems: Algebraic and Semantic Approach</em>, Ph.D. thesis,
University of Warsaw.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1989a, &ldquo;Intuitive semantics for some
three-valued logics connected with information, contrariety and
subcontrariety&rdquo;, <em>Studia Logica</em>, 48: 565&ndash;575.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1989b, &ldquo;Consistency, Completeness and
Negations&rdquo;, in G. Priest, R. Routley, and J. Norman (eds.),
<em>Paraconsistent Logic: Essays on the Inconsistent</em>,
328&ndash;368, Munich: Philosophia Verlag.</li>

<li>Varzi, A.C. and M. Warglien, 2003, &ldquo;The Geometry of
Negation&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Applied Non-Classical Logics</em>,
13:9&ndash;19.</li>

<li>Wagner, G., 1994, <em>Vivid Logic: Knowledge-Based Reasoning with
Two Kinds of Negation</em>, Lecture Notes in Computer Science Volume
764, Berlin: Springer.</li>

<li>Wansing, H., 1993, <em>The Logic of Information Structures</em>,
Lecture Notes in AI 681, Berlin: Springer.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1994, &ldquo;Sequent calculi for normal
modal propositional logics&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Logic and
Computation</em>, 4: 125&ndash;142.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash; (ed.), 1996, <em>Negation. A Notion in
Focus</em>, Berlin: de Gruyter.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2001, &ldquo;Negation&rdquo;, in L. Goble
(ed.), <em>The Blackwell Guide to Philosophical Logic</em>,
415&ndash;436, Oxford: Blackwell Publishers.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2005, &ldquo;Connexive modal logic&rdquo;,
in R. Schmidt et al. (eds.), <em>Advances in Modal Logic. Volume
5</em>, 367&ndash;383, London: King&rsquo;s College Publications.
 [<a href="http://www.aiml.net/volumes/volume5/" target="other">Wansing 2005 also available online</a>]</li>
 
<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2006, &ldquo;Contradiction and contrariety.
Priest on negation&rdquo;, in J. Malinowski and A. Pietruszczak
(eds.), <em>Essays in Logic and Ontology</em>, 81&ndash;93, Amsterdam:
Rodopi.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2008, &ldquo;Constructive negation,
implication, and co-implication&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Non-Classical
Logics</em>, 18: 341&ndash;364.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2016a, &ldquo;Falsification, natural
deduction, and bi-intuitionistic logic&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Logic
and Computation</em>, 26: 425&ndash;450 (first online 2013).</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2016b, &ldquo;On split negation, strong
negation, information, falsification, and verification&rdquo;, in K.
Bimb&oacute; (ed.), <em>J. Michael Dunn on Information Based
Logics</em>, 161&ndash;189: Dordrecht: Springer.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, forthcoming, &ldquo;Beyond paraconsistency.
A plea for a radical breach with the Aristotelean orthodoxy in
logic&rdquo;, to appear in Abilio Rodrigues, Henrique Antunes, and
Alfredo Freire (eds.), <em>Walter Carnielli on Reasoning,
Paraconsistency, and Probability</em>, Cham: Springer.</li>

<li>Wansing, H. and D. Skurt, 2018, &ldquo;Negation as cancellation,
connexive logic, and qLPm&rdquo;, <em>Australasian Journal of
Logic</em>, 15: 476&ndash;488.</li>

<li>Wason, P.C., 1965, &ldquo;The contexts of plausible denial&rdquo;,
<em>Journal of Verbal Learning and Verbal Behavior</em>, 4:
7&ndash;11.</li>

<li>Wason, P.C. and S. Reich, 1979, &ldquo;A verbal illusion&rdquo;,
<em>Quarterly Journal of Experimental Psychology</em>, 31:
591&ndash;7.</li>

<li>Weiss, Y., 2021,&ldquo;Semantics for pure theories of connexive
implication&rdquo;, <em>The Review of Symbolic Logic</em>, 15:
591&ndash;606,</li>

<li>Wilson, D., 1975, <em>Presupposition and Non-Truth-Conditional
Semantics</em>, New York: Academic Press.</li>

<li>Wittgenstein, Ludwig, 1953, <em>Philosophical Investigations</em>,
trans. E. Anscombe, New York: Macmillan.</li>

<li>Wood, L.M., 1933, &ldquo;The paradox of negative judgment&rdquo;,
<em>Philosophical Review</em>, 42: 412&ndash;23.</li>

<li>van der Wouden, T., 1996, <em>Negative Contexts: Collocation,
Polarity, and Multiple Negation</em>, London: Routledge.</li>

<li>von Wright, G.H., 1959, &ldquo;On the logic of negation&rdquo;,
<em>Societas Scientiarum Fennica, Commentationes
Physico-Mathematicae</em>, 22: 1&ndash;30.</li>

<li>Wu, H. and M. Ma, 2023, &ldquo;An infinity of intuitionistic
connexive logics&rdquo;, in M. Banerjee and A.V. Sreejith, (eds.),
<em>Logic and Its Applications. 10th Indian Conference, ICLA
2023</em>, Cham: Springer, 189&ndash;206.</li>

<li>Zalta, E., 2024, &ldquo;The metaphysics of Routley star&rdquo;,
<em>Australasian Journal of Logic</em>, 21: 141&ndash;176.</li>

<li>Zeijlstra, H., 2004, <em>Sentential Negation and Negative
Concord</em>, Utrecht: LOT.</li>

<li>Z&uuml;fle, M. and R. Katzir, 2022, &ldquo;Reasoning about stored
representations in semantics using the typology of lexicalized
quantifiers&rdquo;, <em>Proceedings of Sinn und Bedeutung</em>, 26:
923&ndash;944.</li>

<li>Zwarts, F., 1998, &ldquo;Three types of polarity&rdquo;, in F.
Hamm and E. Hinrichs (eds.), <em>Plural Quantification</em>,
177&ndash;238. Dordrecht: Kluwer.</li>
</ul>
